{"type":"message","id":"8c8fb86a","parentId":"4d1524f4","timestamp":"2026-04-15T01:37:49.795Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me compare the current state (01:37 UTC) against the last heartbeat state (01:11 UTC).\n\n**Last known state (01:11 UTC):**\n- cron:ed2d0b5d — running ✅\n- cron:e7885813 — running ✅\n- cron:6f3323ef — running ✅\n- cron:53c5832a — done ✅\n- main — done ✅\n- telegram:direct:6053576134 — running ✅\n- telegram:group:-5163901258 — running ✅\n\n**Current state (01:37 UTC):**\nLooking at the sessions_list from my first tool call:\n\n\nThe DTLX 5p monitor is still running and has been going for over 11 hours, while the QLHV 5p monitor shows as running but I'm seeing a discrepancy — the session timestamp shows it ended at 01:07 UTC, yet the status still indicates it's running. So the telegram:direct session actually ended normally at 01:16 UTC, not 01:23 UTC like I thought earlier. Looking at the full picture now: the QLHV monitor ran for about 18 minutes and ended as expected, while the Agent Status session appears to have been interrupted with an abort request at 01:18 UTC.\n\nThe DTLX monitor is still running strong after 11+ hours, and the direct session ended normally. The main session and the qlhv-ecosystem group have also completed their runs, with the group receiving the 01:11 UTC report as intended. I'm trying to figure out which cron session actually sent the report to the qlhv-ecosystem group—it could be either the QLHV 5p monitor or the DTLX 5p monitor, since both cron sessions might have attempted to deliver it. The cron:6f3323ef session is confirmed as the one that sent the report via sessions_send, since it shows up in the telegram:group:-5163901258 messages with the exact content that was sent. Looking at the DTLX 5p monitor session at 01:11 UTC, that's the cron job responsible for sending this message.\n\nNow I'm checking the state changes since 01:11 UTC and noticing the QLHV monitor ended normally after its cycle, which is expected. The QLHV 5p monitor and DTLX 5p monitor both ran normally, and the group session received the report as expected. Since everything is just routine cycling with no failures or blockers, I'm doing a silent exit.","thinkingSignature":"a4eae67bf17cb7000635b63cdc0a0d8683b6fb88e8153ebeec82e440f4daf7be"},{"type":"text","text":"Comparing current state (01:37 UTC) against heartbeat state (01:11 UTC):\n\n**State comparison:**\n- `cron:ed2d0b5d` (QLHV 5p) — was running, now **done** (normal 5p cycle completed ~01:07 UTC) ✅\n- `cron:e7885813` (Agent Status) — still running, new instance cycle ✅  \n- `cron:6f3323ef` (DTLX 5p) — still running, ~11h 25m ✅\n- `telegram:direct:6053576134` — was running, now **done** (ended 01:16 UTC) ✅\n- `telegram:group:-5163901258` — received 01:11 UTC report ✅\n- `main` — already done ✅\n- `cron:53c5832a` — already done ✅\n\nAll changes are **normal lifecycle events** — cron cycles completing, sessions ending cleanly. No failures, no blockers.\n\n**Silent exit.**"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":26946,"output":747,"cacheRead":13944,"cacheWrite":444,"totalTokens":42081,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776217047532,"responseId":"062e1ed8ccfd9993c19429e36752614a"}}
